Hydra Sectioned Master Roadmap
Purpose
This roadmap breaks the Hydra project into aligned sections so development can continue in parallel without losing architectural integrity. The goal is not to shrink the vision. The goal is to preserve the vision while making implementation tractable.
This roadmap assumes the following are already true: - The project is one system, not a set of unrelated experiments. - The constitutional layer is upstream of implementation. - The codebase is unevenly mature across sections. - Product proofs should emerge from the architecture, not define it. - Alignment matters as much as progress.
________________________________________
Project Thesis
Hydra is a governed AI middleware and knowledge-economy architecture built around enforced boundaries, versioned knowledge, entitlement-aware access, and post hoc auditability. APP is an exploratory search lane inside that architecture, not the whole architecture. OpenClaw is the current host substrate, not the long-term identity of the system.
________________________________________
The Seven Sections
1. Constitutional Core
What it is
The non-negotiable source of truth for what Hydra is, what it protects, what it forbids, and what claims it is allowed to make.
Includes - Rule Zero - patent framing - constitutional outlines - lexicography - invariants - roadmap authority - drift rules
Primary purpose
Preserve architectural identity across versions, contributors, and implementation waves.
Authority docs - RULE_ZERO.md - MASTER_README.md - current/vckb/docs/CONSTITUTIONAL_MASTER_OUTLINE_V3_0.md - patent materials under current/vckb/docs/ and current/vckb/source_docs/
Current state
Strong conceptually. Weak operationally only in the sense that authority is spread across multiple documents and status claims are not centralized.
Must guarantee - One canonical statement of system purpose - One canonical lexicon - One canonical record of architectural invariants - One canonical roadmap and version status source
Must never do - Drift into feature chatter - Be bypassed by README claims or code comments - Allow product rhetoric to redefine constitutional meaning
Proof target
Every system section can point to a clear constitutional parent and no two authority docs contradict each other materially.
________________________________________
2. Kernel
What it is
The governed runtime control plane: inbound governance, outbound governance, envelope logic, replay, dispatch, telemetry, and fail-closed execution behavior.
Includes - GEL - EGL / Exit Portal - envelope generation and validation - dispatch bridge - telemetry - replay - output gate behavior - OpenClaw interception layer
Primary purpose
Make the claim of enforced boundaries and replayable audit real.
Authority docs - MASTER_README.md - current/gel/README.md - current/egl/README.md - constitutional sections covering GEL/EGL
Current state
Farthest along. Core inbound governance, policy evaluation, VCKB loading, envelope generation, telemetry, and replay already exist in some form. EGL exists as a defined architecture and code package, but integration maturity is still behind the conceptual framing.
Must guarantee - No governed inbound flow without policy evaluation - No governed outbound flow without egress validation - Replay can reconstruct key execution facts - Telemetry is append-only and legible - Default stance remains deny/fail-closed
Must never do - Ask the model to self-authorize - Allow hidden egress paths - Collapse logging and enforcement into one vague behavior
Proof target
A governed OpenClaw session can be shown where ingress, envelope generation, egress, and replay all function as one auditable boundary.
________________________________________
3. DLC / Identity and Entitlement
What it is
The credential and entitlement spine that binds model identity, personal identity, and entity identity into one validation event.
Includes - DLC token assembly - multi-PIN logic - component encryption - validation - issuance assumptions - entitlement scope - liability hooks
Primary purpose
Convert governance from local policy logic into a durable identity-and-rights mechanism.
Authority docs - constitutional outline V3.0 - patent documents related to dual authentication / DLC evolution - future DLC implementation spec
Current state
Constitutionally central, implementation-light. Token validation stubs and design framing exist, but the full cryptographic spine is not yet the live engine of the system.
Must guarantee - No access without valid assembly - No partial token assembly accepted - Components remain independently secured - Validation is auditable - Scope is explicit and machine-checkable
Must never do - Revert to ambient access - Allow silent privilege expansion - Treat entitlement as a prompt-level convention
Proof target
A real token assembly and validation flow denies incomplete credentials and permits only the destinations associated with the active profile.
________________________________________
4. VCKB / Knowledge Economy Substrate
What it is
The version-controlled, provenance-aware, rights-managed knowledge layer.
Includes - AKMs - source docs - retrieval manifests - provenance - version-specific retrieval - author/publisher attribution - compensation logic - future marketplace behavior
Primary purpose
Turn knowledge access into a governed, attributable, and eventually compensable substrate.
Authority docs - MASTER_README.md - constitutional outline sections for VCKB - patent docs under current/vckb/docs/ - VCKB source docs and manifests
Current state
Architecturally strong, partly implemented. Loader behavior exists. Full economy rails and rich publisher flow do not.
Must guarantee - Every retrieval can be versioned and traced - Authoritative knowledge can be distinguished from ambient context - Retrieval inputs are reconstructable after the fact - Knowledge use can be attributed and later priced
Must never do - Degrade into generic untracked RAG - Lose source/version coupling - Let convenience bypass provenance
Proof target
A single model output can be tied back to a versioned knowledge manifest showing exactly what authoritative knowledge was used.
________________________________________
5. APP / Pattern Search Engine
What it is
The exploratory lane for substrate-aware pattern analysis and candidate pattern modification.
Includes - FM1 pattern mapper - modification SLMs - FM2 scorer - adversarial lane - review lane - pattern librarian - Patternzandria / Panternzandria - output labels for epistemic class
Primary purpose
Generate structured novelty without contaminating governance lanes.
Authority docs - APP paper - machine-intuition / lane behavior text - Hydra architecture framing where APP is placed inside lane logic - future APP implementation contract
Current state
Most conceptually distinctive. Least mature operationally. The lane logic is well articulated, but the engine is still mostly scaffolding and stubs.
Must guarantee - APP outputs are clearly labeled as exploratory - Search and scoring remain distinct roles - Failures are archived, not discarded - Candidate patterns are evaluated against substrate and persistence logic - APP outputs never silently inherit governance authority
Must never do - Masquerade exploratory outputs as validated truth - Collapse into ordinary prompt creativity with grandiose labels - Lose failed outputs that contain transferable structure
Proof target
For at least one domain, Hydra produces a pattern map, multiple substrate modifications, a scored shortlist, and a saved archive entry that preserves both good and failed candidates.
________________________________________
6. Garage / AI Space / Capability OS
What it is
The human-facing operating model for context-separated AI identities, permissions, memory boundaries, and destination access.
Includes - Garage - vehicles - keys - destinations - personality policy - memory boundaries - corridor/portal design - AI Space user framing
Primary purpose
Translate the constitutional and entitlement architecture into a usable control model for actual people.
Authority docs - MASTER_README.md - current/vckb/docs/PERMISSION_PORTAL_DESIGN_V3_0.md - future Garage/AI Space UX spec
Current state
Conceptually rich, still design-heavy. This is already one of the clearest product surfaces in writing, but not yet a real runtime operating layer.
Must guarantee - Memory remains scoped by vehicle/profile - Personality is treated as policy, not flavor text - Destination permissions are explicit - Vehicle configuration drift is versioned and auditable
Must never do - Blur work/home/medical contexts - Treat memory bleed as acceptable - Let the same credential silently pick up broader powers without trace
Proof target
One user can switch between at least two profiles with clearly separated memory, destinations, and behavior rules, while the system can show why each boundary held.
________________________________________
7. Product Proofs
What it is
The visible forms of the architecture that prove the system matters in practice.
Includes - OpenClaw-hosted demos - Vibe Coder - Expert-in-a-Box - AI Space demos - scenario walkthroughs - proof-of-value materials
Primary purpose
Make the architecture legible to other people without requiring them to read the whole doctrine first.
Authority docs - MASTER_README.md - VISION.md - scenario docs and future demo specs
Current state
Mixed. Some product ideas already exist in working or semi-working forms, but they are not yet governed by a single proof strategy.
Must guarantee - Each proof showcases a real architectural claim - Demos do not overstate what is still stubbed - Product narratives remain downstream of the system architecture
Must never do - Become the de facto source of truth for the architecture - Promise more than the current system can reconstruct or enforce - Turn APP novelty into the sole public identity of Hydra
Proof target
At least one demo cleanly shows governed execution, and at least one demo cleanly shows controlled exploratory pattern search.
