Recommended Active Tracks
Hydra should not try to advance all sections equally.
Active Track A — Kernel hardening
Reason: this is the strongest proof that boundaries and audit are real.
Focus now - unify GEL and EGL as one governed runtime story - harden replay and telemetry - normalize envelope behavior - remove ambiguity about output gate vs egress enforcement - produce one end-to-end governed session demo
Active Track B — DLC implementation spine
Reason: entitlement is a constitutional pillar and cannot remain mostly rhetorical forever.
Focus now - token component encryption - multi-PIN assembly - validation path - fail states - interface with kernel checks
Active Track C — APP proof-of-novelty demo
Reason: APP is the attention engine and the distinctive research wedge.
Focus now - real FM1 path - at least one modification generator - minimal FM2 scorer - saved archive entries for both promising and failed outputs - explicit label classes for exploratory outputs
Keep warm, not primary
•	full VCKB economy rails
•	Garage / AI Space UX
•	broad product expansion
These should keep evolving in writing and interface thinking, but not dominate implementation until Tracks A–C are tighter.
