Sequenced Roadmap
Phase 0 — Reality Lock
Goal: establish a single truthful map of the current system.
Deliverables: - one canonical project status board - one section ownership map - one authoritative version table - one reality-vs-vision chart - one drift log
Exit condition: No major component has contradictory status claims across top-level docs.
Phase 1 — Kernel Proof
Goal: prove enforced boundaries and replayable audit end-to-end.
Deliverables: - governed ingress demo - governed egress demo - envelope trace sample - replay reconstruction sample - telemetry schema freeze v1
Exit condition: A single governed run can be reconstructed from logs and envelopes.
Phase 2 — DLC Proof
Goal: make entitlement real.
Deliverables: - component format - encryption/decryption flow - multi-PIN assembly - validation endpoint or module - denial behavior examples
Exit condition: Invalid or partial credentials fail closed in the actual runtime path.
Phase 3 — APP Proof
Goal: show useful exploratory pattern search under controlled separation.
Deliverables: - substrate map output - candidate modification set - scorer output - labeled exploratory classes - first Patternzandria archive entries
Exit condition: A domain example shows structured novelty, not just clever prose.
Phase 4 — VCKB Proof
Goal: show versioned knowledge as a governed substrate.
Deliverables: - retrieval manifest format - attribution trace - version lock demonstration - source-level audit example - compensation schema draft linked to real retrieval events
Exit condition: A single output can be tied to specific authoritative versions with visible provenance.
Phase 5 — Garage / AI Space Proof
Goal: make context-separated identity legible to real users.
Deliverables: - vehicle schema - profile switching demo - scoped memory demonstration - destination controls - plain-language explanation layer
Exit condition: Two profiles with different permissions and memory boundaries can be shown without bleed.
Phase 6 — Product Proof Packaging
Goal: make the architecture easy to understand without flattening it.
Deliverables: - one kernel demo - one APP demo - one VCKB demo - one product walkthrough deck or README set - one clean explainer for OpenClaw-based proof
Exit condition: A new viewer can understand the system from artifacts before reading patents or deep doctrine.
